    "num": "09",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">09</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Common Misconceptions</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Avoiding Confusion Around 'Texican'</h2><ul><li>Not synonymous with 'Texian' or 'Texan'</li><li>Not exclusively an ethnic label—includes political allegiance</li><li>Usage depends on historical period and context</li><li>Avoid projecting modern identities onto historical terms</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Misunderstanding 'Texican' can lead to inaccurate historical interpretations; recognizing its specific context is essential. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Mistaking an Anglo settler in 1830s Texas as a 'Texican' ignores ethnic and political distinctions.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify statements that incorrectly use 'Texican' and explain why.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Applying the term without regard to time period or cultural background.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide9\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following best defines the term &#39;Texican&#39; as used historically?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;A settler of Mexican heritage living in Texas during the Mexican period&quot;,&quot;A Native American tribe in Texas&quot;,&quot;An Anglo-American colonist who settled Texas after independence&quot;,&quot;A modern Texan citizen&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:0,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The term &#39;Texican&#39; historically refers to settlers of Mexican heritage in Texas during the Mexican period, distinguishing them from Anglo settlers and later Texans.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain how the settlement patterns and lifestyle of the Texicans reflected their cultural background and the political environment of Mexican Texas.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;A strong answer will describe the Mexican land grant system, family and community life, interactions with indigenous peoples, and how these factors illustrate Texican cultural identity and adaptation to frontier conditions.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Texicans settled primarily through Mexican land grants, establishing ranches and farms that reflected Mexican traditions. Their lifestyle included close-knit family units and cooperation with indigenous groups, showing a blend of cultural heritage and frontier adaptation under Mexican governance.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Texicans settled under Mexican land grants and maintained Mexican cultural traditions in family and community life&quot;,&quot;Their lifestyle involved ranching and farming influenced by Mexican customs and frontier realities&quot;,&quot;They interacted with Native American tribes and adapted to the political context of Mexican Texas&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
