    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">20</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Identity</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Cultural Practices and Traditions</h2><ul><li>Texicans maintained Mexican customs in language, dress, and festivals</li><li>Catholicism was central to cultural identity</li><li>Blended indigenous and Mexican culinary and artistic traditions</li><li>Community events reinforced shared heritage and social bonds</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican culture was a vibrant blend of Mexican traditions and indigenous influences, expressed through religion, language, and social customs that fostered a strong communal identity (s8, s9). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> During a community fiesta, Texicans celebrated with traditional music, food, and religious ceremonies reflecting their blended heritage.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify cultural elements that illustrate the fusion of Mexican and indigenous influences in Texican life.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing Texican culture as purely Mexican without indigenous contributions.</p></div></div>",
