    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">21</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Map Exercise</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Analyzing Texican Settlement Locations</h2><ul><li>Use provided maps showing land grants and settlements</li><li>Identify patterns in settlement clustering near rivers</li><li>Note proximity to indigenous territories and trade routes</li><li>Consider how geography influenced lifestyle and defense</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Mapping exercises help visualize how Texican settlements were strategically placed considering legal, cultural, and environmental factors, deepening understanding of frontier dynamics (s7, s8). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Learners examine a map highlighting settlements along the Rio Grande and discuss why these locations were chosen.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Mark three settlement sites on the map and explain the advantages of each location.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Focusing only on natural resources without considering legal or cultural settlement constraints.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide21\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following best defines the term &#39;Texican&#39; as used historically?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;A settler of Mexican heritage living in Texas during the Mexican period&quot;,&quot;A Native American tribe in Texas&quot;,&quot;An Anglo-American colonist who settled Texas after independence&quot;,&quot;A modern Texan citizen&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:0,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The term &#39;Texican&#39; historically refers to settlers of Mexican heritage in Texas during the Mexican period, distinguishing them from Anglo settlers and later Texans.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain how the settlement patterns and lifestyle of the Texicans reflected their cultural background and the political environment of Mexican Texas.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;A strong answer will describe the Mexican land grant system, family and community life, interactions with indigenous peoples, and how these factors illustrate Texican cultural identity and adaptation to frontier conditions.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Texicans settled primarily through Mexican land grants, establishing ranches and farms that reflected Mexican traditions. Their lifestyle included close-knit family units and cooperation with indigenous groups, showing a blend of cultural heritage and frontier adaptation under Mexican governance.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Texicans settled under Mexican land grants and maintained Mexican cultural traditions in family and community life&quot;,&quot;Their lifestyle involved ranching and farming influenced by Mexican customs and frontier realities&quot;,&quot;They interacted with Native American tribes and adapted to the political context of Mexican Texas&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
