    "eyebrow": "Application",
    "num": "24",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">24</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Application</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Applying Knowledge: Planning a Texican Settlement</h2><ul><li>Use criteria from Mexican land grant programs</li><li>Select a suitable geographic location considering resources and defense</li><li>Design community layout reflecting family and religious life</li><li>Plan strategies for indigenous relations and security</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This application exercise challenges learners to apply their understanding by designing a hypothetical Texican settlement that meets historical and cultural requirements (s7, s8, s9). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Learners propose a settlement near a river with a central mission, clustered family homes, and militia organization for defense.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Create a settlement plan that balances legal, cultural, geographic, and security factors discussed in this section.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Neglecting one or more critical factors such as legal requirements or indigenous relations in the plan.</p></div></div>",
