    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">56</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Application</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Analyzing Primary Sources on Texican Multicultural Life</h2><ul><li>Examine excerpts from letters, land grants, and community records</li><li>Identify evidence of cultural interactions and blended practices</li><li>Evaluate source reliability and perspectives</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Applying knowledge to primary sources helps learners critically analyze historical evidence of Texican multicultural life and understand the complexities of frontier identities. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A land grant document may reveal Spanish legal language alongside references to indigenous land use practices.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze a provided primary source excerpt and describe multicultural elements present.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Avoid taking sources at face value; consider context and potential biases.</p></div></div>",
